<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="76" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="5.[322,802,801,844]" box="[347,778,825,844]" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">
<heading box="[347,778,825,844]" centered="true" fontSize="36" level="2" pageId="5" pageNumber="76" reason="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[347,778,825,844]" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[352,457,825,844]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
: Leiodidae, Cholevinae, Cholevini)
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[148,977,873,1080]" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">
When describing 
<emphasis box="[339,532,873,894]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">Catops meridionalis</emphasis>
Peck and Cook (2002:772) of the southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[148,279,899,920]" name="United States of America" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">United States</collectingCountry>
, we overlooked the fact that the name is a homonym of 
<emphasis box="[828,977,899,920]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">C. meridionalis</emphasis>
Aubé (1850:326). We thank our colleague Michel Perreau for bringing this to our attention. We therefore provide the replacement name 
<emphasis box="[689,920,953,974]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">Catops neomeridionalis</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[936,977,952,973]" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">new</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="76" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[148,977,873,1080]" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[148,204,979,1000]" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">name</emphasis>
, for 
<emphasis box="[254,450,979,1000]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">Catops meridionalis</emphasis>
Peck and Cook 2002 (not 
<emphasis box="[720,917,979,1000]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">Catops meridionalis</emphasis>
Aubé (1850)). We note that 
<emphasis box="[377,530,1006,1027]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">C. meridionalis</emphasis>
Aubé has long been recognized as a junior synonym of 
<emphasis box="[267,421,1032,1053]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">C. marginicollis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lucas" box="[427,603,1032,1053]" pageId="5" pageNumber="76" refId="ref2316" refString="Lucas, H. P. 1846. Exploration scientifique de l'Algerie pendant les annes 1840, 1841, 1842, publiee par ordre du gouvernement et avec le concours d'une commission academique. Sciences Physiques, Zoologie. Deuxieme partie. Paris: Imprimerie national. 580 pp." type="book" year="1846">Lucas (1846: 224)</bibRefCitation>
, and it is known from 
<collectingCountry box="[817,890,1032,1053]" name="Algeria" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">Algeria</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[900,973,1032,1053]" name="Tunisia" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[190,250,1059,1080]" name="Egypt" pageId="5" pageNumber="76">Egypt</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
